Those traveling long distances this holiday season can expect to pay for a number of tolls on South Africa’s major roads. According to the official toll tariffs effective as of March 2017, it will cost a Class 1 vehicle (all light vehicles) R240.00 to travel from Pretoria/Johannesburg to Durban, while a trip made from Pretoria/Johannesburg to Cape Town would set you back R164.50 in the same vehicle. You can find a calculation of the most popular toll routes detailed below.        Images courtesy of Drive South Africa. Read: Sanral sees major increase in motorists using electronic tolls